# kui-react — Cursor rules

Canonical source: [AGENTS.md](mdc:AGENTS.md). When Cursor and AGENTS.md disagree, AGENTS.md wins.

## Before writing code, fetch the catalog

1. `GET /api/registry?index=1` — every component, theme, design token, and convention. ~5x smaller than the full registry.
2. `GET /api/registry` — same shape with full source code per component + variants.
3. `GET /llms-full.txt` — markdown dump of the full registry.
4. Offline fallback: `public/registry/components.json` (built by `npm run registry:snapshot`).

Search recipe:

```ts
const reg = await fetch('/api/registry?index=1').then(r => r.json());
const matches = reg.components.filter(c =>
  c.layer === 'domain' && c.filePath.includes('/commerce/') && /card/i.test(c.name)
);
```

Follow `composes[]` recursively to know what other files to copy when porting a component. `usedBy[]` is the inverse index.

## ⚠️ Catalog sync — REQUIRED

**Any time you add, rename, or remove a component (`modules/ui/`, `modules/app/`, `modules/domains/<vertical>/`), a theme (`app/theme/<vertical>/`), a showcase section file, or a `showcase.menu.ts` entry, run:**

```bash
npm run registry:snapshot
```

**before committing.** This regenerates `public/registry/components.json` + `public/registry/components.index.json` + `public/components/*.md` from the showcase data. The same script runs automatically via the `prebuild` npm hook before `npm run build`, but you must still commit the regenerated files so the catalog stays in lockstep with the code. A stale catalog misleads every AI agent that reads it — treat it as broken-build severity.

## Hard rules

1. **`'use client';`** at the top of every file in `modules/ui/`, `modules/app/`, `modules/domains/`. Theme `layout.tsx` is client; theme `page.tsx` is server unless it owns local state.
2. **Named exports only.** No default exports (excluding `next/dynamic` wrappers).
3. **`cn()` for classNames.** Import from `@/libs/utils/cn`. Never template-literal or string-concat classes.
4. **Token-only styling.** Reference CSS-variable tokens (`bg-primary`, `text-text-secondary`, `border-border-focus`). Never raw hex / rgb / hsl.
5. **Icons: Font Awesome only.** Named imports from `@fortawesome/free-solid-svg-icons` / `free-brands-svg-icons`. No `lucide-react`, `heroicons`, `react-icons`, inline SVG, or emoji as icons.
6. **Accessibility every time:**
   - `focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-border-focus` on interactive elements
   - `aria-busy` / `aria-invalid` / `aria-describedby` / `aria-pressed` / `aria-expanded` where applicable
   - `disabled:opacity-50 disabled:cursor-not-allowed`
   - `aria-hidden="true"` on decorative `<FontAwesomeIcon>`
7. **Spread `...rest`** to the root element so consumers can pass through HTML attributes.
8. **No business logic in `modules/ui/`** — data fetching, routing, external calls go in `modules/app/` or `modules/domains/`.

## Where new code goes

| What you're building | Where |
| --- | --- |
| Single-purpose atom (button, input) | `modules/ui/` |
| Composed molecule (card, modal) | `modules/ui/` |
| Full page section / shell / form | `modules/app/` |
| Industry-specific component | `modules/domains/<vertical>/` |
| New industry vertical | `modules/domains/<vertical>/` + `modules/showcase/data/sections/domain-<vertical>.showcase.tsx` + add to `modules/showcase/data/showcase.menu.ts` |
| Full multi-page demo | `app/theme/<vertical>/` |

## Path aliases

- `@/` — project root
- `@/modules/ui/<Component>` — atoms + molecules
- `@/modules/app/<Component>` — organisms + page shells
- `@/modules/domains/<vertical>` — industry vertical barrel
- `@/libs/utils/cn` — className utility

## Component template

```tsx
'use client';
import { cn } from '@/libs/utils/cn';

type MyComponentVariant = 'primary' | 'secondary';

const variantClasses: Record<MyComponentVariant, string> = {
  primary:   'bg-primary text-primary-fg hover:bg-primary-hover',
  secondary: 'bg-secondary text-secondary-fg hover:bg-secondary-hover',
};

type MyComponentProps = {
  variant?: MyComponentVariant;
  children?: React.ReactNode;
  className?: string;
} & React.HTMLAttributes<HTMLDivElement>;

export function MyComponent({ variant = 'primary', children, className, ...rest }: MyComponentProps) {
  return (
    <div
      className={cn(
        'rounded-md px-4 py-2 font-medium transition-colors',
        'focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-border-focus',
        variantClasses[variant],
        className,
      )}
      {...rest}
    >
      {children}
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Don't

- Don't install new icon libraries.
- Don't introduce a CSS-in-JS runtime (styled-components, emotion). Tailwind + CSS variables only.
- Don't fetch real data inside a `modules/ui/` component.
- Don't write a new component if one already exists in the registry — extend or compose instead.
